name: DialogRoot
description: Groups all parts of the dialog. Doesnâ€™t render its own HTML element.

animated.description:
If `true`, the dialog supports CSS-based animations and transitions.
It is kept in the DOM until the animation completes.

defaultOpen.description:
Determines whether the dialog is initally open.
This is an uncontrolled equivalent of the `open` prop.

dismissible.description: Determines whether the dialog should close when clicking outside of it.

modal.description: Determines whether the dialog is modal.

onOpenChange.description: Callback invoked when the dialog is being opened or closed.

open.description: Determines whether the dialog is open.
